{{Infobox country telephone plan | country = Iraq | country_link = Iraq | continent = Asia | map_image = Iraq (orthographic projection).svg | map_caption = | map_size = 500px | map_alt = | country_calling_code = +964 | international_prefix = 00 | trunk_prefix = 0 | regulator = | plan_membership = | nsn_length = | dial_plan_type = closed | number_format = | codes_list = }}
Iraq area codes can be 1 or 2 digits (not counting the trunk prefix 0) and the subscriber numbers are usually 6 digits. In Baghdad and some other governorates, they are 7 digits. The mobile numbers have 10 digits, beginning with the 3-digit code of each operator followed by 7 digits.
